text:
~ Just a little observation on Gura ~

So i watched the entire resident evil: village play-through so far which was like 14 hours long all in all, and I realized what made it so fun to sit through was that she played the game with maximum immersion and as if she were in the game itself. Her personality and dialogue were literally merged into Ethan Winters. 

Most people just walkthrough a game just as is. But when she plays, you wouldn‚Äôt know what to expect because she says stuff in-stream as if she were in the situation of the Main Character. She speaks and taunts the enemies, talks to Duke in such a fun way, makes fun of the people in the village, and interacts with the world as if she were in it.

Her talent to make the game more fun by putting her own dialogue and personality in the setting is what sets her apart to most streamers. She is such a gift to the streaming community. Big thumbs up!

text:
Youtube really decided to crash this party. Some tips for troubleshooting problems like this:
1. Type "Is youtube down" into your preferred search engine. There are websites dedicated to tracking and mapping service outages like this. If there's been a surge in issues, you'll see it. Please don't spam "LAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAG" in the chat.
2. Refreshing is usually a good first step, but they only fix issues if they're from your computer. If it's not your computer giving you trouble, refreshing will not help. Please don't spam "JuST prEsS F5 DuM dUm" in the chat.
3. If you're not having problems, that does not mean there are no problems. That just means your region is not having a problem, so just enjoy the stream. Please don't spam "It works fine for me" in the chat.
4. If you have found a solution, letting other's know is fine, but remember your solution is not necessarily going to work for everyone. Please don't spam the chat with your solution.
5. Really guys, just don't spam the chat.
